TSMC has issued bonds for its new plant in Arizona, according to a letter of intent, which will raise a total of about $3.5 billion.  
  
TSMC completed the pricing and sold four kinds of bonds, which will raise about 3.5 billion US dollars. This is TSMC's first dollar bond issuance since October last year. It is reported that this batch of bonds ranges from 5 to 30 years, of which the 5-year bonds are priced at the same-year U.S. Treasury bonds plus 100 basis points. The 7-, 10-, and 30-year U.S. dollar bonds are priced at 120, 135 and 150 basis points over the same-year U.S. Treasury bond, respectively.
